<subSubSection id="FECE839F907964B1787D21132432E37C" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="comments">
<paragraph id="C64B8E8ED26644473A6B18383A27FA40" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="770B3FA50E3FE105D288BF2C86B81558" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
With 177 named species, this is the largest genus within 
<taxonomicName id="DFBEA76ADD13A99871546F92434385E4" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1881" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Zodariinae">Zodariinae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C05AB38B7C6D7AF1D0F69EE51548D4D8" author="WSC" journalOrPublisher="Trudy Soveta po Izuceniju Proizvoditeljnych Sil, Serija Turkmenskaja" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" publicationUrl="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" refId="B26" refString="WSC, 2021. World Spider Catalog. Version 21.5. Natural History Museum Bern, http://wsc.nmbe.ch" title="World Spider Catalog. Version 21.5. Natural History Museum Bern," url="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" year="2021">WSC 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Based on the copulatory organs of the species currently considered in this genus, 
<taxonomicName id="B3FA8F757BAE53D3B79F767ECACF0022" authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1826" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zodarion" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="515E6BA3F5881C9037F4ADCF4569B76B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Zodarion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not appear to be monophyletic. There are only two species that are morphologically similar to the generotype: 
<taxonomicName id="DC0AE2A849AC5F3D8C255AB65F217583" genus="Z." lsidName="Z. luctuosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="luctuosum">
<emphasis id="F48A6AB60F66F3BBE2A2DEB115D5537E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Z. luctuosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872) and 
<taxonomicName id="0A42897BDB14512B2D3DDC403E6EEB0D" genus="Z." lsidName="Z. lutipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="lutipes">
<emphasis id="49C06D8660EA049914C72E95F23C302F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Z. lutipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872), from the eastern Mediterranean (east of Tunisia to Iran).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
